parameters.description: Log of COTS intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_cots ≈ 2.0, representing potential for rapid population growth during outbreaks.
Log of COTS carrying capacity (individuals/m²). Corresponds to K_cots ≈ 2.0, representing maximum sustainable density during outbreaks.
Log of COTS natural mortality rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to m_cots ≈ 0.5, representing average annual mortality rate.
Log of COTS predation rate on fast-growing coral (m²/individual/year). Corresponds to alpha_fast ≈ 0.3, representing higher preference for Acropora species.
Log of COTS predation rate on slow-growing coral (m²/individual/year). Corresponds to alpha_slow ≈ 0.1, representing lower preference for Faviidae and Porites species.
Log of fast-growing coral intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_fast ≈ 0.8, representing rapid growth of Acropora species.
Log of slow-growing coral intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Corresponds to r_slow ≈ 0.2, representing slower growth of Faviidae and Porites species.
Log of fast-growing coral carrying capacity (%). Corresponds to K_fast ≈ 50%, representing maximum potential cover of Acropora species.
Log of slow-growing coral carrying capacity (%). Corresponds to K_slow ≈ 50%, representing maximum potential cover of Faviidae and Porites species.
Log of competition coefficient of slow on fast coral (dimensionless). Corresponds to beta_fast ≈ 0.5, representing moderate competitive effect.
Log of competition coefficient of fast on slow coral (dimensionless). Corresponds to beta_slow ≈ 0.5, representing moderate competitive effect.
Log of optimal temperature for COTS reproduction (°C). Corresponds to temp_opt ≈ 28°C, based on observed outbreak patterns.
Log of temperature tolerance width for COTS reproduction (°C). Corresponds to temp_width ≈ 2°C, representing temperature range for successful reproduction.
Log of scaling factor for immigration effect (dimensionless). Corresponds to imm_effect ≈ 1.0, scaling the impact of larval immigration.
Log of coral cover threshold affecting COTS survival (%). Corresponds to coral_threshold ≈ 10%, representing minimum coral cover needed for COTS population maintenance.
Log of strength of coral effect on COTS survival (dimensionless). Corresponds to coral_effect ≈ 1.0, determining steepness of response to coral availability.
Log of standard deviation for COTS observations. Corresponds to sigma_cots ≈ 0.2, representing observation error.
Log of standard deviation for fast coral observations. Corresponds to sigma_fast ≈ 5%, representing observation error.
Log of standard deviation for slow coral observations. Corresponds to sigma_slow ≈ 5%, representing observation error.
Vector of years for time series data
Sea surface temperature (°C)
COTS larval immigration rate (individuals/m²/year)
Observed COTS adult abundance (individuals/m²)
Observed fast-growing coral cover (%)
